Preheat your oven to 200°C and bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil on
medium-high heat with 0.5 tsp of @salt{}. Pop the @Tuscan Pork Sausage{4} on a
#baking tray{} and bake on the top shelf of your #oven{} until brown and cooked
through, ~{20-25%minutes}, turning halfway through cooking.

> TIP: The sausages are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, add the @Linguine{200%g} to the boiling water and simmer until the
pasta is tender, ~{12%minutes}. When the pasta is cooked, ladle out some of
the cooking water into a #bowl{} and reserve @Reserved Pasta Water for the Sauce{200%ml}.

> This reserved pasta water is for the sauce.

Then drain the pasta in a #colander{}, pop it back in the pan and drizzle with
@oil{} and mix through to stop it sticking together.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and chop the @Onion{1}(halved, peeled and chopped) into
small pieces. Halve the @Fennel{1} through the root, remove the triangular root
and then thinly slice (similar to if you were slicing an onion). Roughly chop
the @Flat Leaf Parsley{1%bunch}(roughly chopped, stalks and all).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium high heat. Once hot, add
the onion, stir and cook for ~{2%minutes}, then add the fennel and cook, stirring
occasionally until it's beginning to soften, ~{5-6%minutes}. Add the
@Tomato Puree{60%g}, stir and cook for ~{1%minute}, then pour in the reserved
pasta cooking water. Stir in the @Chicken Stock Powder{1}, bring to a simmer,
cover the pan with a #lid{} or some #kitchen foil{}.

Simmer the sauce until the fennel is really nicely softened, ~{5-7%minutes}.
Meanwhile, once the sausages are cooked, remove them from the oven and chop up
into rounds about 1cm thick with a #knife{} and #fork{}. Once the fennel is
softened, remove the lid and stir in the @Unsalted Butter{30%g}, half the
@Grated Hard Italian Style Cheese{40%g} and half the parsley. Stir until the
butter and cheese are melted, then stir in the sausages and remove from the heat.

Taste the sauce and add @salt{} and @pepper{} if you feel it needs it. Add the
pasta to the sauce and toss together (or add the sauce and sausages to the
pasta depending on what's easier). Serve in #bowls{} with the remaining parsley
and cheese sprinkled on top. Enjoy!